 {"id":"markdown_web_browser-cls","content_hash":"15ffa6dadfd1fff567e2f7f605267e0150ce7aa10008b02fe5669fc9a2b6090e","title":"Profile_id passthrough & persistent contexts","description":"PLAN §4.1 (POST /jobs), §5 (profile chooser), and §7 (persistent browser profiles + manifest flags) require that `profile_id` travel from the UI/CLI into capture so authenticated sessions live under isolated Chromium directories. Today the API schemas accept `profile_id`, the UI and CLI send it, but `JobManager`/`capture_tiles` ignore it, so every job still runs in a transient profile.

Tasks:
- Thread `profile_id` through `JobCreateRequest`, `JobManager`, and `capture` so each job can reuse `~/.mdwb/profiles/<id>` directories, including manifest + RunRecord metadata (`manifest.profile_id`).
- Enforce safe directory names, create the profile directory on demand, and add retention policies + tests.
- Update docs/PLAN/README to describe how operators configure profiles, the new manifest field, and the security guidance for red/blue separation.
